a_n=(-\frac{1}{2})^n
a_n
\;n\;
\left\{\frac1{2^{2n}}\right\}_{n\in\Bbb N}=\left\{\frac14\,,\,\frac1{16}\,,\,\frac1{64}\,,\ldots\,,\frac1{4^n}\,,\ldots\right\}
\frac{\frac1{4^{n+1}}}{\frac1{4^n}}=\frac14
\frac{\frac14}{1-\frac1{4}}=\frac13
\;n\;
\left\{-\frac1{2^{2n-1}}\right\}_{n\in\Bbb N}=\left\{-\frac12\,,\,-\frac18\,,\,-\frac1{32}\,,\ldots\,,\,-\frac2{2^{2n}}\,,\ldots\right\}
\frac{-\frac2{2^{2(n+1)}}}{-\frac2{2^{2n}}}=\frac14
\frac{-\frac12}{1-\frac14}=-\frac23
n\geqslant0
a_{2n}=r^n,\qquad a_{2n+1}=b\cdot r^n, 
 b=-\frac12,\qquad r=\frac14,
 \sum_{n=0}^\infty a_{2n}=\frac1{1-r}=\frac43\qquad\sum_{n=0}^\infty a_{2n+1}=\frac{b}{1-r}=-\frac23, 
 \sum_{n=0}^\infty a_{n}=\frac43-\frac23=\frac23. 
